New York, May 5th 1876
Dear Jennie;
Your letter has made me very sad, and anxious also about the loved ones at home. It almost makes me want to run home & help Dr. Wms. take care of the sick ones. How does Anna stand it? I feel anxious about her as also about you all. How is Hugh Jones? He has been in my mind very much since your letter came. He was so much exhausted, the disease must have taken severe hold.
